Definition:
Connectors (also called linking words or connectives) are words or phrases used to join sentences,
clauses, or ideas and show the relationship between them.

Types of Connectors (very important for exams)

1. Addition (extra information)
Used when you’re adding more points.
Name =  and, also, moreover, furthermore, in addition, besides
 Example: She is intelligent and hardworking.

